I"b <p>Sadly till rowing the bachelor’s boat and this is a self made south indian recipe, <strong>The exclusive dried anchovies pickle curry</strong>. This goes well with boiled rice as a main course and also as a side dish for chapathis and parathas. A typical <strong>Tamil</strong> dish by heart. Give it a try! <br /><br />The preparation time is approximately 20 minutes. You will find a brief step-by-step method on how to make this recipe. So let’s get started.</p>

<h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Dried Anchovies (50 - 100 gms)</li>
  <li>Olive Oil - 3 Tbsp</li>
  <li>Ginger Garlic Paste - 1 Tbsp</li>
  <li>Onions x2</li>
  <li>Tomatoes x2</li>
  <li>Chillies x3</li>
  <li>Curry Leaves x7</li>
  <li>Fennel Seeds - 1 Tsp</li>
  <li>Cumin Seeds - 1 Tsp</li>
  <li>Mustard Seeds - 1 Tbsp</li>
  <li>Tumeric Powder - 1/2 Tsp</li>
  <li>Chilli Powder - 3/4 Tsp</li>
  <li>Coriander Powder - 1/4 Tsp</li>
  <li>Salt to Taste</li>
</ul>

<hr />

